  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11498">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Explain the need for bird study and why birds are useful indicators of the
      quality of the environment. Describe how birds are part of the ecosystem.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-QUbQCn-ViA" target="_blank"
        >Why Are Birds Important (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_FooquV6Cbs" target="_blank"
        >Why Birds Matter (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11499">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Show that you are familiar with the terms used to describe birds by doing
      the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11499 mb-requirement-id-11500">
        (a) Sketch or trace a perched bird and then label 15 different parts of
        the bird. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gD9TAt1F17A" target="_blank"
          >How to Draw and Label a Bird (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11499 mb-requirement-id-11501">
        (b) Sketch or trace an extended wing and label six types of wing
        feathers. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HqZCj_ykfYk" target="_blank"
          >Bird Wing Anatomy - Underside (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TGiIlwnaNmM" target="_blank"
          >Bird Wing Anatomy - 2 (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11502">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Demonstrate that you know how to properly use and care for binoculars, a
      spotting scope, or a monocular.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11502 mb-requirement-id-11503">
        (a) Explain what the specification numbers mean on binoculars, a
        spotting scope, or a monocular. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g3ewVm-46g0" target="_blank"
          >Selecting Your First Binoculars for Birdwatching - the 5 Things You
          Need to Know (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11502 mb-requirement-id-11504">
        (b) Show how to adjust the eyepiece and how to focus for proper viewing.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pkPzl-VPmo4%20" target="_blank"
          >How to Get Crystal Clear Focus With Your Binoculars (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cNx9klskWFk" target="_blank"
          >How to Use Binoculars For Bird Watching - A Beginners Guide!
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11502 mb-requirement-id-11505">
        (c) Show how to properly care for and clean the lenses. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z5DaExac1e0" target="_blank"
          >How to Clean Your Binoculars (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11502 mb-requirement-id-11506">
        (d) Describe when and where each type of viewing device would be most
        effective. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://chirperbirds.com/spotting-scope-vs-binoculars-for-birdwatching/"
          target="_blank"
          >What's the Difference-Spotting Scope vs Binoculars for Birdwatching
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
